 1→//axhob_operation
 2→{rbtgo_ark_conjure}
 3→
 4→NOTE: This operation conjures an
 5→{rbtga_ark}
 6→in
 7→{rbtgi_repository}
 8→by building a container image from a vessel specification and assembling build provenance metadata. The
 9→{rbtr_director}
10→performs the build via
11→{gcb_service}.
12→
13→NOTE: This is the ark-level view of the build operation. For detailed build procedure steps, see
14→{rbtgo_trigger_build}.
15→
16→The conjure operation:
17→
18→//axhop_parameter_from_type
19→{rbtgr_vessel_dir}
20→. *Validate Input Parameters*:
21→.. {rbbc_require}
22→vessel directory provided as first argument
23→.. {rbbc_require}
24→vessel contains conjuring configuration (RBRV_CONJURE_DOCKERFILE, RBRV_CONJURE_BLDCONTEXT)
25→
26→//axhos_step
27→. *Execute Build*:
28→.. Delegate to
29→{rbtgo_trigger_build}
30→which dispatches via the vessel's
31→{rbtgr_vessel_trigger}
32→.. All build parameters baked in
33→{rbtgr_build_json}
34→— zero custom substitution overrides
35→.. Waits for build completion
36→.. On success, both
37→{rbtga_ark_image}
38→and
39→{rbtga_ark_about}
40→artifacts are created with shared
41→{rbtga_consecration}
42→.. {rbtgr_provenance}
43→is auto-generated by Google as a signed attestation on the built image
44→
45→//axhoo_output_of_type
46→{rbtga_ark}
47→. *Display Results*:
48→.. {rbbc_show}
49→vessel image built with consecration tag
50→
51→//axhoc_completion
52→Successful execution creates a complete
53→{rbtga_ark}
54→with both image and about artifacts sharing the same
55→{rbtga_consecration}.
56→

 1→//axhob_operation
 2→{rbtgo_image_retrieve}
 3→
 4→NOTE: This operation retrieves a container image from
 5→{rbtgi_repository}
 6→to the local container runtime. The
 7→{rbtr_retriever}
 8→has read-only access to the repository.
 9→
10→The
11→{rbtr_retriever}
12→pulls an image by {rbst_locator}:
13→
14→//axhop_parameter_from_type
15→{rbst_locator}
16→. *Validate Input Parameters*:
17→.. {rbbc_require}
18→`«INPUT_LOCATOR»` provided as first argument in `moniker:tag` format
19→.. {rbbc_fatal}
20→if missing: "Locator parameter required (moniker:tag)"
21→.. {rbbc_fatal}
22→if malformed (no colon): "Invalid locator format. Expected moniker:tag"
23→.. {rbbc_store}
24→`«MONIKER»` as portion before first colon
25→.. {rbbc_store}
26→`«TAG»` as portion after first colon
27→
28→//axhos_step
29→. *Authenticate as
30→{rbtr_retriever}*:
31→.. Execute
32→{rbtoe_retriever_authenticate}
33→.. {rbbc_store}
34→`«RETRIEVER_TOKEN»` for subsequent operations
35→
36→//axhos_step
37→. *Construct Registry Reference*:
38→.. {rbbc_store}
39→`«REGISTRY_HOST»` as `{rbrr_gcp_region}-docker.pkg.dev`
40→.. {rbbc_store}
41→`«FULL_IMAGE_REF»` as `«REGISTRY_HOST»/{rbrr_depot_project_id}/{rbrr_gar_repository}/«INPUT_LOCATOR»`
42→
43→//axhos_step
44→. *Configure Container Runtime Authentication*:
45→.. {rbbc_call}
46→container runtime login with:
47→... registry: `«REGISTRY_HOST»`
48→... username: `oauth2accesstoken`
49→... password: `«RETRIEVER_TOKEN»`
50→.. {rbbc_require}
51→login successful
52→.. {rbbc_fatal}
53→if login fails: "Container runtime authentication failed"
54→
55→//axhos_step
56→. *Pull Image*:
57→.. {rbbc_call}
58→link:https://github.com/opencontainers/distribution-spec/blob/main/spec.md#pulling-manifests[Docker Registry API: pull] via container runtime:
59→... command: `docker pull «FULL_IMAGE_REF»` or `podman pull «FULL_IMAGE_REF»`
60→.. {rbbc_require}
61→pull completes successfully
62→.. {rbbc_store}
63→`«IMAGE_ID»` from pulled image metadata
64→.. {rbbc_fatal}
65→if pull fails: "Image pull failed"
66→
67→//axhoo_output_of_type
68→{rbtgi_image}
69→. *Display Results*:
70→.. {rbbc_show}
71→image retrieved: `«FULL_IMAGE_REF»`
72→.. {rbbc_show}
73→local image ID: `«IMAGE_ID»`
74→
75→//axhoc_completion
76→Successful execution retrieves the image and displays the local image ID.
77→

  1→//axhob_operation
  2→{rbtgo_retriever_create}
  3→
  4→The
  5→{rbtr_governor}
  6→creates a
  7→{rbtr_retriever}
  8→{giam_service_account}
  9→with read-only
 10→{rbtgi_repository}
 11→access:
 12→
 13→//axhoq_precondition
 14→* Execute {rbtoe_check_rubric_repo_url} (validates {rbrr_rubric_repo_url} using PAT from Secret Manager)
 15→
 16→//axhoq_precondition
 17→* Execute {rbtoe_check_cbv2_connection} to verify {rbtgi_cbv2_connection} is active
 18→
 19→//axhop_parameter_from_type
 20→{rbtr_retriever}
 21→. *Validate Input Parameters*:
 22→.. {rbbc_require}
 23→`«INPUT_INSTANCE»` provided as first argument
 24→.. {rbbc_store}
 25→`«RETRIEVER_ACCOUNT_NAME»` as `retriever-«INPUT_INSTANCE»`
 26→.. {rbbc_store}
 27→`«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` as `«RETRIEVER_ACCOUNT_NAME»@{rbrr_depot_project_id}.iam.gserviceaccount.com`
 28→
 29→//axhoq_precondition
 30→* {rbbc_require}
 31→`BURD_OUTPUT_DIR` environment variable set and directory exists
 32→
 33→//axhos_step
 34→. *Authenticate as
 35→{rbtr_governor}*:
 36→.. Execute
 37→{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
 38→.. {rbbc_store}
 39→`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls
 40→
 41→//axhos_step
 42→. *Create
 43→{rbtr_retriever}
 44→Service Account*:
 45→.. {rbbc_call}
 46→link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/create[iam.serviceAccounts.create] with:
 47→... accountId: `«RETRIEVER_ACCOUNT_NAME»`
 48→... displayName: `Recipe Bottle Retriever («INPUT_INSTANCE»)`
 49→... description: `Read-only access to Google Artifact Registry - instance: «INPUT_INSTANCE»`
 50→... project:
 51→{rbrr_depot_project_id}
 52→.. {rbbc_require}
 53→HTTP 200 response
 54→.. {rbbc_store}
 55→`«RETRIEVER_UNIQUE_ID»` from response `.uniqueId` field
 56→
 57→//axhos_step
 58→. *Verify Service Account Propagation*:
 59→.. {rbbc_call}
 60→link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/get[iam.serviceAccounts.get] for `projects/-/serviceAccounts/«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»`
 61→.. {rbbc_poll}
 62→with backoff until HTTP 200 (newly-created SA may not be immediately resolvable by email)
 63→.. NOTE: Poll must use the email address, not the numeric ID. The email-based lookup path has independent propagation from the UID-based path, and subsequent steps (keys.list, keys.create) all use the email address. Polling by UID can succeed while the email path still returns 404.
 64→.. {rbbc_require}
 65→service account accessible by email
 66→
 67→//axhos_step
 68→. *Preflight: Ensure Pristine Key State*:
 69→.. {rbbc_call}
 70→link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/list[serviceAccounts.keys.list] for `«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»`
 71→.. {rbbc_store}
 72→`«EXISTING_KEYS»` from response `.keys[]`
 73→.. {rbbc_require}
 74→no keys with `keyType: USER_MANAGED` exist
 75→.. {rbbc_fatal}
 76→if USER_MANAGED keys found: "Manual cleanup required via Console"
 77→
 78→//axhos_step
 79→. *Generate Service Account Key*:
 80→.. {rbbc_call}
 81→link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/create[serviceAccounts.keys.create] for `«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` with:
 82→... privateKeyType: `TYPE_GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_FILE`
 83→.. {rbbc_store}
 84→`«RETRIEVER_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` from response `.privateKeyData` field
 85→.. {rbtoe_rbra_generate}
 86→converts `«RETRIEVER_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` to `«RETRIEVER_RBRA_FILE»`
 87→
 88→//axhos_step
 89→. *Grant
 90→{rbtgi_repository}
 91→Read Access*:
 92→.. {rbbc_call}
 93→link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/setIamPolicy[projects.setIamPolicy] for
 94→{rbrr_depot_project_id}
 95→.. Add `serviceAccount:«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` with role:
 96→... `roles/artifactregistry.reader` (read-only access to all Artifact Registry repositories)
 97→.. Policy version: 3
 98→.. {rbbc_require}
 99→IAM policy update successful
100→
101→//axhoo_output_of_type
102→{rbtgi_rbra_file}
103→. *Display Installation Instructions*:
104→.. {rbbc_show}
105→Retriever created successfully
106→.. {rbbc_show}
107→RBRA file location: `«RETRIEVER_RBRA_FILE»`
108→.. {rbbc_show}
109→installation command:
110→... `cp "«RETRIEVER_RBRA_FILE»" "{rbrr_retriever_rbra_file}"`
111→.. {rbbc_warn}
112→if
113→{rbrr_retriever_rbra_file}
114→already exists
115→
116→//axhoc_completion
117→Successful execution creates retriever service account with read-only Artifact Registry access and provides RBRA file installation command.
118→
